{"id":"joktan","term":"Joktan","source":"International Standard Bible Encyclopaedia (James Orr ed., 1915)","html":"<p>jok'-tan (yoqTan, meaning unknown): \"Son\" of Eber, and \"father\" of 13 tribes (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:25\">Ge 10:25</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:26\">26</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:29\">29</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 1:19\">1Ch 1:19</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 1:20\">20</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 1:23\">23</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 10:25","Genesis 10:26","Genesis 10:29","1 Chronicles 1:19","1 Chronicles 1:20","1 Chronicles 1:23"]}